She specializes in the field of Mathematics, Statistics and Data Analytics.

Dr. Mark Daevid Adem is a full-time faculty member from the College of Hospitality and Tourism Management. He has been teaching for 14 glorious years in the Hospitality Management Program at the Trinity University of Asia located at E. Rodriguez Sr. Avenue, Quezon City, Philippines. He earned his Bachelor's Degree in Hotel and Restaurant Management at Trinity University of Asia (2008) graduated with Latin honors Magna Cum Laude and was Nominated for the Trinitarian of the Year in the same year. He earned his Master's in Business Administration at Trinity University of Asia (2019). While completing his master's degree, he received a scholarship grant for the "Study Abroad Program" at Kobe International University, Kobe Japan, in partnership with the Trinity University of Asia from April 2017 to March 2018.

  On July 28, 2022, Dr. Adem finished his doctorate, Doctor of Philosophy in International Hospitality and Tourism Management at the Lyceum of the Philippines University (Batangas). He received honorary recognition as the 2nd Highest Academic Excellence Awardee. He is also a Certified Guest Service Personnel by the American Hotel & Lodging Educational Institution. He also gained Certification in Hotel Industry Analytics from STR in partnership with AHLEI. For this academic year, he is handling Hospitality Management Courses such as Thesis Writing, Environmental Science with Sustainable Hospitality, Front Office, and Kitchen Essentials with Basic Food Selection.

Ms. Dawnie Dela Cruz is an alumna of Trinity University of Asia (TUA) and one of the pioneer batch of Psychometrician Board passers in 2014 earned her Master’s Degree in St. Paul University Quezon City (SPUQC) and got her license as Psychologist last year. She joined Trinity University of Asia early this year as Part-time Associate Professor in College of Arts, Sciences and Education (CASE) Psychology Department. In January 2020, Professor Dawn was invited with "Bawal Judgemental” one of the primetime noon show’s segments as their guest Clinical Psychologist to tackle some LGBTQ issues and concerns and the same year was awarded as one of the “Top 10 Most Outstanding Alumni “in Trinity University of Asia.

Recently, she co-founded the Lifemap Psychological Consultancy and currently serves as its Psychologist and Consultant. She loves attending conferences, workshops and trainings related to Psychology while traveling at the same time. Some of her trainings and expertise revolves around projective techniques, psychological assessment and creative psychological report writing. She also co-hosts and organized various seminars and trainings about stress debriefing, stress management, resiliency and mindfulness lastly, despite her hectic schedule she plans to pursue her Doctorate degree in Forensic Psychology anytime soon.

Mr. Steve Michael M. Moore Jr. is a graduate of Bachelor of Arts major in Communication Arts at the University of Santo Tomas. He also finished his Master of Arts in Communication at the UST Graduate School.

Mr. Moore was the Marketing Officer of the University of Santo Tomas from 2007 to 2019. He handled the Marketing and Promotions unit of the University under the Office for Admissions (OFAD). He has 14 years of solid managerial experience in the field of School Marketing, Public Relations and Customer Service. In 2017, He also served as the Marketing Consultant of Chyrus Marketing Inc, the sole local distributor of Cowhead Milk products in the Philippines. In 2020, he joined the De La Salle-College of Saint Benilde as their Admissions External Relations Head. 


He is also a distinguished resource speaker in the field of Marketing Communications. He conducted seminars in different parts of the country about various professional topics like School Marketing Strategies, The Role of Communication in the fields of Science and Tourism, Internal Marketing in the Academe, Marketing Presentation Strategies, Social Media Literacy and Digital Marketing.

Mr. Moore was also the Co-Founder of S&G events, an event company specializing in coordinating weddings and corporate events. He is also a freelance Theater and Film Actor, Event Director, and Event Host.     

At present, Mr. Moore is the Marketing Director of De La Salle College of St. Benilde. He is also a part time College Instructor at the University of Santo Tomas where he teaches Sport Marketing & Communications under the Institute of Physical Education and Athletics.  Aside from teaching in UST, he also teaches Marketing and Public Relations at Trinity University of Asia under the Department of Media and Communications and also at the Communications Department of De La Salle College of St. Benilde - Antipolo.

Mr. Miguel Garcia, nicknamed Sir Migs, has been an English language and literature teacher since 2009, the year when he earned his Bachelor of Secondary Education major in English degree from the University of Santo Tomas. 

He has taught high school, college, and professional learners in practically all kinds of institutions: public high school, private sectarian and non-sectarian high schools, sectarian and non-sectarian colleges, and public universities.

He participated in the Spoken English Promotion Project of Zhejiang Gongshang University and UST, where he studied Chinese language and culture classes and served as an English language teaching assisstant to Chinese college students.

He finished his Master's in English from the UST Graduate School in 2016. In 2019, he started pursuing a Ph.D. in Applied Linguistics degree in the Br. Andrew Gonzalez, FSC College of Education, De La Salle University.

He has presented his papers in international conferences and published his research. He has also trained teachers, professionals, and graduate students in writing, research, and professional development.

Hi!  I'm Ronn Mikhael A. Avila, MPsy a registered Psychometrician and I will be your professor this semester.

I graduated from Polytechnic University of the Philippines and PUP Graduated School with a Bachelors's and Masters's Degree in Psychology Major in Clinical Psychology. Former Counselor at Department of Health Treatment and Rehabilitation Center Bicutan 2015 - 2018. Currently, I am the Department Head of the Trinity University of Asia - Psychology Department. 


Seminar Speaker and Mental Health Advocate.

I worked as a counselor at the Department of Health Treatment and Rehabilitation Center - Bicutan, Taguig City, Philippines for 4 years.  For the length of my services, I handled thousands of drug dependents but mostly adolescent individuals with substance use disorder and behavioral problems. I'm certified to administer numerous psychological tests from self-report tests to projective tests and trained to facilitate Therapeutic. I'm also a practitioner of Positive Arts Intervention, this method focused to instill self-understanding among patients and encourage them to adopt new attitudes and feelings towards life situations through visual arts.  I used art to be part of the patient's healing process that helping them make small changes to self-defeating behavior and cope with feelings of sadness, fear, and pain can bring life-altering results through art. I also play in a punk band name MNR MJRTY, we play different shows around Metro Manila

Getting to Know Ella

Ella Janine P. Cruz is currently a BS Psychology freshman student at Trinity University of Asia, Quezon City. She finished her basic education studies from elementary to high school at St. Scholastica's Academy of Marikina. She  graduated  from  the Academic Track: Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics (STEM)  strand from School Year 2018-2020.  As an intellectually driven individual who founds curiosity from life and human existence,  Ella is passionate to seek knowledge from various academic paradigms in fields of Psychology, History, Humanities, Arts, Philosophy, Religion, Social Sciences, Biological and Physical Sciences. She tends to see the big picture in every endeavor she dwells without leaving the important details to note from every task. Ella possesses an INTJ-T personality type that values the importance of responsibility in planning & craftsmanship, organization, management skills and critical thinking. She ensures that she was able to accomplish her goals with flying colors.

Ella values artistry in every work, and was highly inclined to visual arts. She was a former board member (SY. 2018-2019)  and secretary (SY. 2019-2020) of Maestra Organization, a visual arts-affiliated club in  SSAM Senior High School Department. She also holds the position of secretary  on Obra Club during her Junior High School years (2017-2018). Being exposed to various modes of visual arts made herself engaged to continuous  mastery of several  art mediums such as  watercolor, digital arts, oil pastel  and color pencils. Ella's art genres focuses on realism, abstractionism, as well as protest arts  and basic anime. She usually joins art contests that made her bagged as the winner of 2018 SSAM JHS MAPEHFEST Celebration, 3rd place in Genyo Nutrition Month Poster making contest (traditional section, 2017) and consolation prize winner for Share your Office Warehouse Story Summer Art Contest (2019).

Ella is also an active  promoter of Filipino culture that encourages her fellow individuals to patronize the maximization of mother tongue and local arts.  She believes that in order to know ourselves, we must first embrace our identity. Ella is a Filipino language enthusiast that enjoys writing anecdotes, novels, academic papers, and similar modes of expression in Filipino language.

Although introverted in nature,  Ella enjoys intellectual conversations that stimulates a balance of objectivity and subjectivity. She ensures to hear both sides of an argument before creating a rash judgment. Moreover, Ella was a woman of advice that most of the people would always tend to rely on for being caring and accommodating to the immediate needs and concerns of her classmates. Ella values humor and relationships to the right people. She ensures that the people closed to her would feel safe and assured. Although an average person with big dreams, she possesses grit and perseverance in achieving her goals. She may never be the typical "math-whiz" person who could calculate easily from the tips of her fingers, but she  is ready to burn the midnight oil when time asks her. She would always strive her best to understand the things she cannot merely comprehend, even if odds go against her.  She will always ensure that in every work she do, there's a standard degree of quality she always maintained through.

Don't be deceived! With her stern looking face all the time, she is still an approachable person someone would definitely enjoy her company. This 18-year old workaholic and semi-bibliophile  student envisions a promising future not only for the betterment of herself, but for the rest of her society.

I'm Edgardo G. Martin III, a 2nd year Medical Technology student. I'm 20 years old and currently living in Bugallon, Pangasinan. 

I chose Trinity University of Asia's College of Medical Technology because of their performances in the past MedTech Licensure Examinations. I also see myself that I will grow here from being a student to becoming a professional someday. The Medical Technology program equips me with the knowledge that I will be needing to pursue my dream as a Medical Doctor. Taking this course is very challenging, you need to indulge yourself in learning and to remain focused no matter what.  In the College of Medical Technology you will learn the right values and conduct to cope with the course, itself. I learned that one big factor to achieve your dreams is to surround yourself with people who have the same goal with you and achieve it together. This is what I always keep in mind and say to myself, ''When you are in difficult times, just look back then you will see that you have come a long way that you are so close to your dreams''.
